com.gams.api

Class GAMSSymbolRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gams.api.GAMSSymbolRecord
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GAMSEquationRecord, GAMSParameterRecord, GAMSSetRecord, GAMSVariableRecord

    public abstract class GAMSSymbolRecord
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the representation of a single record of a GAMSSymbol instance. Derived classes are GAMSEquationRecord, GAMSParameterRecord, GAMSSetRecord and GAMSVariableRecord.
    See Also:
    GAMSSymbol.addRecord(String...), GAMSSymbol.deleteRecord(String...), GAMSSymbol.getFirstRecord(), GAMSSymbol.getFirstRecord(String...), GAMSSymbol.getLastRecord(), GAMSSymbol.getLastRecord(String...), GAMSSymbol.findRecord(String...), GAMSSymbol.mergeRecord(String...)

      • moveNext

        public boolean moveNext()
        Iterate to next GAMSSymbolRecord of GAMSSymbol using the current criterion. In case of a specific criterion has been specified, such as retrieving record in GAMSSymbol that meets a slice criteria (GAMSSymbol.getFirstRecord(String...)}) the method returns the next GAMSSymbolRecord that also meets the criteria. Otherwise the method returns the next sequential GAMSSymbolRecord.
        Returns:
        true if successfully moved to the next record, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        GAMSException - if the GAMSDatabase instance has already been disposed.
        Since:
        24.1.3
        See Also:
        extends GAMSSymbolRecord>.getFirstRecord(String...), extends GAMSSymbolRecord>.getLastRecord(String...)

      • movePrevious

        public boolean movePrevious()
        Iterate to previous GAMSSymbolRecord of GAMSSymbol using the current criterion. In case of a specific criterion has been specified, such as retrieving record in GAMSSymbol that meets a slice criteria (GAMSSymbol.getLastRecord(String...)), the method returns the previous GAMSSymbolRecord that also meets the criteria. Otherwise the method returns the previous sequential GAMSSymbolRecord.
        Returns:
        true if successfully moved to the previous record, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        GAMSException - if the GAMSDatabase instance has already been disposed.
        Since:
        24.1.3
        See Also:
